Subject: Re: [T2] Heater questions (replacement of ducting)

On Mon, 4 Nov 2002, Jay Ollom wrote:

> My question is what have folks used as non-stock
> replacements for heater ducting?

Some have used PVC or somesuch, but I don't think it is a good idea.  Home
centers sell galvanized heating duct that might be of use.  Don't forget
to put a blanket of fiberglas around it or you'll be heating the out of
doors, not your feet.

George Lyle
